## ðŸ“š Study Modules

### Phase 1: Foundations (Completed)
- [x] Lab environment setup
- [x] Basic networking concepts
- [x] Linux & Windows command line
- [x] Git and version control
- [x] Ethical hacking framework

### Phase 2: Web Application Security (In Progress)
- [x] HTTP protocol deep dive
- [x] SQL injection fundamentals
- [x] Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- [ ] Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)
- [ ] Authentication vulnerabilities
- [ ] Session management
- [ ] File upload vulnerabilities

### Phase 3: Network Security
- [ ] TCP/IP protocol analysis
- [ ] Network reconnaissance
- [ ] Man-in-the-Middle attacks
- [ ] Wireless security
- [ ] Firewall evasion techniques

### Phase 4: System Exploitation
- [ ] Buffer overflow mechanics
- [ ] Stack vs heap exploitation
- [ ] Return-oriented programming (ROP)
- [ ] Privilege escalation (Linux)
- [ ] Privilege escalation (Windows)

### Phase 5: Post-Exploitation
- [ ] Lateral movement techniques
- [ ] Persistence mechanisms
- [ ] Data exfiltration methods
- [ ] Log manipulation
- [ ] Anti-forensics

### Phase 6: Malware Analysis
- [ ] Static analysis techniques
- [ ] Dynamic analysis in sandbox
- [ ] Behavioral analysis
- [ ] Reverse engineering tools
- [ ] Indicator of Compromise (IOC) development

### Phase 7: Mobile Security
- [ ] Android architecture
- [ ] APK reverse engineering
- [ ] iOS security model
- [ ] Mobile exploitation

### Phase 8: Defense & Detection
- [ ] Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS)
- [ ] Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)
- [ ] Threat hunting methodologies
- [ ] Incident response procedures
- [ ] Forensics fundamentals

