## ðŸš€ Getting Started

### Prerequisites Checklist

**Technical Skills**:
- [ ] Basic programming (Python recommended)
- [ ] Command line proficiency (Linux & Windows)
- [ ] Understanding of networking fundamentals
- [ ] Version control basics (Git)

**Hardware Requirements**:
- Minimum 16GB RAM (32GB ideal)
- 100GB+ free disk space
- Virtualization-capable CPU
- Stable internet connection

**Software Requirements**:
- VirtualBox or VMware
- Git
- Python 3.8+
- Text editor (VS Code, Sublime, etc.)

### Setup Process

**1. Clone This Repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/defensive-security-lab.git
cd defensive-security-lab
```

**2. Review Learning Plan**
```bash
# Check out the current study modules
cat learning-notes/study-plan.md
```

**3. Set Up Lab Environment**
```bash
# Follow detailed lab setup guide
./scripts/lab-setup.sh
```

**4. Create Initial VM Snapshots**
```bash
# Snapshot all VMs in clean state
./scripts/vm-snapshot.sh create-baseline
```

**5. Start Learning!**
```bash
# Begin with web security fundamentals
cd learning-notes/lab-exercises/
cat 01-web-fundamentals.md
```

