## ðŸ“ Documentation Approach

### Learning Notes Format

Every study session is documented with:

```markdown
# [Topic Name] - Study Session

**Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
**Duration**: X hours
**Module**: [Current learning module]

## Objective
What I aimed to learn in this session

## Environment Setup
- Target VM: [VM name]
- Tools used: [List]
- Network config: [Setup details]

## Methodology
Step-by-step process of what I did

## Findings
- What worked
- What didn't work
- Unexpected behaviors

## Key Learnings
Main takeaways from this session

## Defensive Insights
How this knowledge applies to defense:
- Detection methods
- Prevention strategies
- Mitigation techniques

## Questions for Further Study
Things I don't understand yet

## References
Resources I used
```

### Code Documentation Standards

All code includes comprehensive comments:

```python
"""
Script: [Name]
Purpose: Learning exercise for [specific concept]
Date: YYYY-MM-DD

Educational Context:
- Demonstrates [attack/vulnerability type]
- Used exclusively in personal lab environment
- Part of study module: [Module name]

Defensive Application:
- Helps understand [attack pattern]
- Informs development of [defensive control]
- Detection signatures: [List relevant indicators]

âš ï¸ LAB USE ONLY - Never use on unauthorized systems
"""
```

